Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.54,0:01:34.73,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,yoake ga osokute jirettai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.75,0:01:34.73,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, Sunshine four...WE GO!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.75,0:01:39.86,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,ichi, ni, Sunshine yon...we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.88,0:01:39.86,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,We...made it this far
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.88,0:01:45.87,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,ore tachi wa...koko made kitaze
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.89,0:01:45.87,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,We go...to where the dream is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.89,0:01:48.74,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,ore tachi wa iku...yume no arika e
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.76,0:01:48.74,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,We won’t left anyone behind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.76,0:01:53.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,dare mo oitekanaize--
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.85,0:01:53.83,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep going forward, that’s our pledge
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.85,0:01:56.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,nshin aru nomi sore ga chikai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.52,0:01:56.50,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Since the day that the dream began
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.52,0:02:00.55,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,yume ga hajimatta ano hi kara
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.57,0:02:00.55,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,the future that I’m \Naiming at hasn’t changed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.57,0:02:04.63,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,mezasu mirai wa onaji--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.65,0:02:04.63,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t stand still, I can’t stop
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.65,0:02:07.30,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,tto dekinai tomarenai
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.32,0:02:07.30,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,The sun of my heart will never set
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.32,0:02:11.52,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,kokoro no taiyou shizumanai
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.54,0:02:11.52,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, Sunshine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.54,0:02:15.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,ichi, ni, Sunshine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.71,0:02:15.69,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, Sunshine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.71,0:02:19.73,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,ichi, ni, Sunshine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.75,0:02:19.73,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, Sunshine four...WE GO!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.75,0:02:27.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,ichi, ni, Sunshine yon...we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.30,0:02:35.29,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,WE GO!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.31,0:02:38.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the pirates who are \Nafter the One Piece...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.73,0:02:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...head for the New World, \Nthe second half of the Grand Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.03,0:02:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, no one has ever fully explored it \Nexcept for Gold Roger, King of the Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.41,0:03:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The New World has ruined many \Npirates' dreams and ambitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.42,0:03:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Monkey D. Luffy, a boy whose body turned \Nto rubber after he ate the Gum-Gum Fruit,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.34,0:03:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and his friends venture into that sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.34,0:03:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna become the King of the Pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.02,0:03:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On their way to the New World,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.56,0:03:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy and his crew reached the Fish-Man \NIsland located 10,000 meters below sea level,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.90,0:03:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where the New Fish-Man Pirates who are \Nlooking to destroy the Ryugu Kingdom...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.66,0:03:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...assisted by Vander Decken, who is after Shirahoshi,\N are engaging in secret maneuvers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.79,0:03:42.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Straw Hats find themselves\N caught up in the turmoil.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.00,0:03:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.88,0:03:56.88,B1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(2000,2000)}"The Sun Pirates Split! Jimbei vs. Arlong!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.89,0:04:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so that was how the captain of \Nthe Sun Pirates - Fisher Tiger died.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.07,0:04:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The captain's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.08,0:04:22.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you all must know \Nhow painful it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.50,0:04:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...for the crew who were left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.31,0:04:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.60,0:04:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Don't kill humans"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.77,0:04:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See what happens when \Nyou show mercy to them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.03,0:04:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother Tai was a fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.03,0:05:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.12,0:05:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.04,0:05:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong-san!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.72,0:05:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't forgive them at any cost!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.65,0:05:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get ready, you bastards!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.65,0:05:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the Fish-Man...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.58,0:05:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So noisy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.26,0:05:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Arlong, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.22,0:06:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What brought you here?\N Why did you come back so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.19,0:06:08.88,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,1)}THE NAVY HQ VICE ADMIRAL\NBORSALINO (FUTURE ADMIRAL KIZARU)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.90,0:06:11.13,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,...nonchalantly?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.15,0:06:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna kill all the people \Nwho betrayed Big Brother Tai!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.66,0:06:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna go to that island too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.37,0:06:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're seeking revenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.79,0:06:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! Fisher Tiger is dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.04,0:06:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You lowly creatures killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.08,0:06:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh I see, he's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.09,0:06:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you need to come with me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.47,0:06:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enraged by Fisher Tiger's death,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.72,0:06:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong lashed out against \Nhumans and he was imprisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.19,0:06:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He could've survived if he hadn't\N been refused a transfusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.99,0:06:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fisher Tiger didn't have to die \Nif there was Fish-Man's blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.53,0:07:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You humans killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.00,0:07:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Fisher Tiger, \Nthe Captain of the Sun Pirates,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.83,0:07:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dies After Being Denied a \NTransfusion of Human Blood."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.34,0:07:16.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not too far from the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.09,0:07:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cause of his death was related to humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.26,0:07:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong told the Navy a lie...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.18,0:07:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth was far more tragic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.43,0:07:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tiger was betrayed by humans so he \Nrefused their blood because he had
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.36,0:07:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,hard feelings against them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.19,0:07:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, he was a slave.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.99,0:07:40.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that became public, \Nit would have stained Boss' honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.91,0:07:48.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why Arlong told a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.46,0:07:53.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain Jimbei! There is an enemy ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.29,0:07:58.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even without the Boss,\N there is no turning back now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.59,0:08:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare for action!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.05,0:08:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't kill anybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.47,0:08:07.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.52,0:08:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I start identifying myself as \N"First Son of the Sea" Jimbei
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.31,0:08:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and as the captain of the Sun Pirates,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.98,0:08:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did nothing but fight, day in and day out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.86,0:08:22.26,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,1)}THE FISHMAN ISLAND - THE RYUGU PALACE
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.28,0:08:24.56,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,"I am writing this because..."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.58,0:08:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"...I thought that you two deserved\N to know the whole truth."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.91,0:08:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Sun Pirates captain - Jimbei."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.92,0:08:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mind is set.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.42,0:08:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess Tiger had no choice but\N to live the way he did-jamon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.76,0:08:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I understand what was going\N through his mind that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.11,0:09:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be alright! I will not give in!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.20,0:09:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We shall live under the sun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.74,0:09:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The day that humans and we \Nunderstand each other will come!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.83,0:09:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sign here to show that you want to relocate!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.63,0:09:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible, Otohime-sama!\N We just can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.67,0:09:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Humans refused to help \NTiger-san who saved slaves
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.55,0:09:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of all races without discrimination!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.64,0:09:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could we understand them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.81,0:09:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another day without any signature.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.69,0:09:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.19,0:09:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My sweet babies!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.74,0:09:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother-sama, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.61,0:09:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay? Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.49,0:09:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look very tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.70,0:09:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're my consolation!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.25,0:09:58.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.13,0:09:59.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.71,0:10:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.88,0:10:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I promise you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.84,0:10:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a great future!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.18,0:10:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Queen Otohime was working\N so hard day after day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.94,0:10:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rescuing humans from shipwrecks...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.99,0:10:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Are you alright?!\N--It was pirates again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.62,0:10:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Help me...\N--Of course, we will help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.00,0:10:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take them to the island!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.54,0:10:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Teaching the island children\N about the world above...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.59,0:10:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I taught you yesterday, this is \Nan area with many trees called forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.05,0:10:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forest? The Sea Forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.97,0:10:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Collecting signatures...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.93,0:10:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.98,0:11:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll only take a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.40,0:11:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.94,0:11:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Queen Otohime!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.49,0:11:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you folk are the ones \Nwho signed it, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.08,0:11:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to ask you a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.29,0:11:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many signatures have you got so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.16,0:11:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have been doing this for 5 years
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.87,0:11:23.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but on about 100 sheets of paper\N there are 10 signatures each.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.17,0:11:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means there are 1000 supporters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.76,0:11:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The population of the Fish-Man Island is \N5 million so, to be honest, I'd prefer more...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.43,0:11:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, here is what we have to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.77,0:11:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're afraid we want to withdraw \Nour signatures - which amount to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.40,0:11:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about half of what you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.23,0:11:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.23,0:11:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't heard yet? \NThe pirates who arrived the other day...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.03,0:12:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...committed a robbery in this \Ntown and got away from the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.50,0:12:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Queen Otohime...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.13,0:12:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Queen Otohime!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.05,0:12:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh kids! Do you want to hear\N about the world above?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.35,0:12:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... My mom wants the paper \Nthat I signed the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.10,0:12:28.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mom wants it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.11,0:12:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.49,0:12:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I listened to you because you're the Queen...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.37,0:12:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we have problems with humans...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.00,0:12:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't wanna...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.75,0:12:47.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Hear your speech anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.21,0:12:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are tired of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.76,0:13:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home, Mother-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.06,0:13:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I worked so hard today! I'm home, my angels!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.32,0:13:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I overdid it... \NCould you leave me alone for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.26,0:13:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are all liars!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.94,0:13:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otohime-sama! You're on the air\N - the whole country heard it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.49,0:13:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shurrup!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.95,0:14:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minister of the Left!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.06,0:14:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you drunk?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.93,0:14:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.06,0:14:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shurrup! I'm not... I'm not drunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.90,0:14:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.90,0:14:36.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What is that?\N--Is that Otohime-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.49,0:14:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody, listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.87,0:14:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We... We are capable of staying \Nin the water forever if we want!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.79,0:14:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in the ocean so broad,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.34,0:14:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and on the seafloor so dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.26,0:15:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we chose to live in this \Nlimited area... Do you know why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.73,0:15:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otohime-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.15,0:15:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it because there is some light and air?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.78,0:15:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there is more light above ground,\N and the sky is higher!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.50,0:15:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do our children sneak \Nout to see the Sabaody Park?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.30,0:15:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are more beautiful places \Nthan we can imagine in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.48,0:15:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no place that we should not go...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.65,0:15:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are just making convenient \Nexcuses to convince yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.03,0:16:02.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and giving everything up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.03,0:16:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have courage!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.16,0:16:11.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And go for what you truly want!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.33,0:16:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Majesty...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.96,0:16:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If humans stand in your way,\N let's face them together!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.63,0:16:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe we can make a difference for \Nthe future of the children on this island,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.14,0:16:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even just a small one!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.00,0:16:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I left my family behind \Non the Fish-Man Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.67,0:16:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My kid and wife... I wonder \Nhow they are doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.38,0:17:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you can go home someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.89,0:17:06.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We former slaves will get\N killed if they find us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.85,0:17:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So whether we want it or not, we have to \Nkeep sailing for the rest of our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.31,0:17:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! I didn't mean it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.86,0:17:21.72,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,1)}THE NAVY HEADQUARTERS
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.74,0:17:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you alright now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.74,0:17:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.74,0:17:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe that you got beaten so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.91,0:17:37.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong, who was locked up in Impel\N down the other day, is nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.09,0:17:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The most violent one is Jimbei!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.05,0:17:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was unbelievably strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.26,0:17:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too dangerous to have him at large.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.18,0:17:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.31,0:17:59.76,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,UNCLEAR JUSTICE
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.78,0:18:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They want me to join the Seven Warlords?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.74,0:18:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your bounty was raised \Nto 250 million berries!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.91,0:18:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They figured that you're gonna be an \Neven bigger threat to the Government.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.71,0:18:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They finally got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.17,0:18:24.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's turn them down and gain \Nmore notoriety, Captain Jimbei!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.17,0:18:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I think I'm gonna take the offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.51,0:18:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.72,0:18:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Jimbei! \NI heard about the Seven Warlords.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.85,0:18:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I join the Warlords, Aladdin and the\N others who don't want to be pirates...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.73,0:18:47.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...can live in this country without being \Nchased under the amnesty of the Government.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.82,0:18:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, if I become a Warlord,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.45,0:18:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Fish-Man can get closer\N to the World Government.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.62,0:19:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the good of the Queen who \Nwe've caused so much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.00,0:19:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.80,0:19:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's not feeling well now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.47,0:19:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it could make the late \NTiger's dream come true -
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.14,0:19:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,liberation and freedom for the Fish-Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.60,0:19:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But at the same time, I think the amnesty\N would cause us some trouble too...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.40,0:19:31.40,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,1)}IMPEL DOWN
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.12,0:19:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Arlong-san!\N--Arlong!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.91,0:19:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.71,0:19:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Arlong-san!\N--Arlong-san is back! He's back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.13,0:19:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.01,0:19:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you've got something to say, just say it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.64,0:19:56.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna join the Warlords,\N huh? Brother Jimbei.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.39,0:20:00.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna be the \NGovernment's dog, aren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.90,0:20:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you remember what Brother Tai said?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.86,0:20:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let resentment and \Nanger get the better of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.07,0:20:11.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotten soft, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.49,0:20:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'd be safe if I just \Nfollowed you, but I refuse!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.75,0:20:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Brother is dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.83,0:20:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll lead the Arlong Pirates again!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.25,0:20:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take my men with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.17,0:20:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.13,0:20:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong, you fool...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.05,0:20:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you really wanna stop\N me, you better kill me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.14,0:20:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.98,0:20:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Arlong-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.40,0:20:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't do it, I'm free to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.90,0:20:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I represent the anger of the Fish-Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.78,0:21:00.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How arrogant you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.96,0:21:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jimbei-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.25,0:21:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.06,0:21:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jimbei-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.52,0:21:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.54,0:21:44.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just take him away now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.71,0:21:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arlong-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.96,0:21:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, Jimbei.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.47,0:21:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You two grew up together and\N he's like a brother to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.85,0:22:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder you couldn't just kill \Nhim even though you were justified.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.68,0:22:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't that fool understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.90,0:22:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...what Brother Tai truly meant?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.48,0:22:16.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wherever he goes, as long as he engages\Nin violence, the Navy won't leave him alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.20,0:22:22.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or if that doesn't work,\N let's go and stop him ourselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.12,0:22:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...at any cost!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.87,0:22:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well, we'll go our own way,\N just like we used to, Captain Jimbei!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.05,0:22:32.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Macro, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.88,0:22:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let them go!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.34,0:22:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.85,0:22:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, he's like a monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.77,0:22:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.82,0:22:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Sun Pirates split into three groups
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.91,0:23:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and went separate ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.13,0:23:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of Jimbei's status \Nas one of the Seven Warlords,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.37,0:23:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he is able to safely bring the \Nformer slave Fish-Men home.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.26,0:23:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as Otohime's ideal future \Nhad seemed one step closer,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.89,0:23:22.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a drifting ship arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.31,0:23:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On board is a Celestial Dragon \Nwho thinks of Fish-Men as
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.56,0:23:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nothing more than slaves!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.19,0:23:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.48,0:23:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shaking Fish-Man Island! \NA Celestial Dragon Drifts In!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.02,0:23:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
